## {{!linkable_header('Green lights for equation evaluation')}}


Try your luck at the Pythagorean Theorem using my website.
Remember, ancient Greek philosopher Pythagoras
theorized that for any right triangle (a triangle with 
one 90 degree angle), that sum of the squares of the two 
shorter angles equals the square of the hypotenuse (longest side).  
Remember, the evaluation of each answer will be done by a computer program.
Therefore the _normal_ computer operators will be used.
