Variable names are **case sensitive**.
Therefore, use lower-case $a$, $b$, and $c$, for the following equations.
Using an upper-case version of the variables will result in an <font color="red">unknown: No globals A</font> message.

<div class="row">
 <div class="threefourthcolumns">
<b>Pythagorean.Theorem.1</b>: Given a right triangle with sides 
$a$ of length 3 and $b$ of length 4, what is the length of 
hypotenuse $c$?  
% answer = 'sqrt(a*a + b*b)'
{{!expression(answer, dict(a=3, b=4), points=10, name='Pythagorean.Theorem.1')}}<br/>
% include('viewAnswer')

<p/>
Note that an acceptable answer can use 
numerical equations like $3**2 + 4**2$.
Or the answer can be use
symbolical values in equations like $a**2+b**2$.
Or the answer can use number integer values like 5.

<p/>
Each correct solution will be highlighted in <font color='green'>green</font> whenever 
the answer is finished.
The system assumes input is finished when you click outside the input box.
